I got it.

161
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,830
Sir, hello.

162
00:09:58,880 --> 00:09:59,670
Can you repair my phone?

163
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,230
What's wrong with it?

164
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:02,750
The call goes through,

165
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:03,630
but the screen is blank.

166
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,070
It can be fixed,

167
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,670
but your phone is too old.

168
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:08,750
Its parts are hard to find.

169
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:12,110
I've been to several stores.

170
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,910
If you have any channels,
can you help me ask around?

171
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:15,870
I can pay more.

172
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:17,230
Why bother?

173
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,030
Look at all these phones I have.

174
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,230
Just pick another one.

175
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,830
No need, thanks.

176
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,870
Ms. Fang, I've been doing it
just like you taught me.

177
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,630
Why does it keep opening?

178
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,630
You're slow.

179
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,750
I made it into a pie already.

180
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:33,950
Come on, make another one.

181
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,550
Is this how I taught you?

182
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,070
You need to use some water.

183
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:37,790
Use some water?

184
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,550
So it can be sealed tightly.

185
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:40,390
Then...

186
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,630
It's too much.

187
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,270
No.

188
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:43,510
